---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Terms of Service | ZeroUpload";
const description =
  "The terms of service for using ZeroUpload, the free in-browser file converter.";
const updated = "June 2026";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-16 pb-20">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-stone">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="article-body mt-8 space-y-4 text-stone leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">1. Acceptance of terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing or using ZeroUpload (the "Service"), you agree to these Terms
        of Service. If you do not agree, please do not use the Service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">2. The Service</h2>
      <p>
        ZeroUpload provides free, browser-based file conversion tools. All
        conversions are performed locally on your own device. The Service is
        provided free of charge for personal and commercial use.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">3. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to use ZeroUpload only with files you have the legal right to
        convert, and not for any unlawful purpose. You are solely responsible for
        the files you process and the results you produce. You agree not to misuse
        the Service or attempt to disrupt its operation.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">4. No warranty</h2>
      <p>
        THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE," WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF
        ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO
        WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND
        NON-INFRINGEMENT. While we work hard to provide accurate, reliable
        conversions, we do not warrant that every conversion will be error-free,
        lossless, or suitable for your particular purpose.
        <strong>Always keep a copy of your original files.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">5. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, ZEROUPLOAD AND ITS OPERATORS SHALL
        NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR
        PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF DATA, PROFITS, OR GOODWILL, ARISING FROM
        YOUR USE OF (OR INABILITY TO USE) THE SERVICE. Because your files are
        processed only on your own device and are never uploaded to us, we never
        hold or control them.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">6. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The ZeroUpload name, branding, and site content are the property of their
        respective owners. The Service is built on open-source software, used in
        accordance with its respective licenses.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">7. Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may revise these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the Service
        after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">8. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of Dhaka, Bangladesh, without regard
        to its conflict-of-law provisions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink">9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Email <strong>support@zeroupload.app</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-body :global(strong) {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
